# TypeScript rules

## Layout

- `src/cli.ts` — thin entry; delegate to `src/cli/run.ts`.
- `src/commands.ts` — single source of truth for command names; update tests when adding commands.
- `src/version.ts` — `TOOL_NAME` and `VERSION`; bump `package.json` on release.

## Imports

- Use `import … from "./foo.js"` (`.js` suffix for ESM resolution).
- Export public API from `src/index.ts` when adding library surface.

## Tests

- Colocate tests as `*.test.ts` next to the module under test.
- Prefer testing pure functions and CLI helpers over full AWS integration in unit tests.
- Mock AWS SDK / Athena at boundaries; do not require live AWS credentials in CI.

## AWS integration (when implementing)

- Read credentials/profile from CLI flags and `~/.config/bdusage/config.toml` per SPEC.
- Athena queries: filter `line_item_product_code = 'AmazonBedrock'`; principal filter via `line_item_iam_principal`.
- Surface actionable errors; route setup problems to `doctor` messaging where SPEC defines it.

## Build

- Production bundle via `build.ts` (Bun.build); declarations via `tsc --emitDeclarationOnly`.
- CLI artifact: `dist/cli.mjs` with shebang banner.
